The Imperius curses were used for &quot;the Greater Good&quot;, so to speak, by Harry
and McGonagall. The Cruciatus was indeed &quot;more unforgivable&quot;, compared to
the others, but Harry was under extreme provocation.

In GoF it's mentioned that Barty Crouch Sr. authorised the use of
Unforgivables by Auror, during the first War with Voldemort. Presumably
after his &quot;downfall&quot; at Godric's Hollow, the authorisation was withdrawn.
In which case the use of these curses by Harry and McGonagall would have
been illegal. That subsequently neither got a life-term in Azkaban proves
that the extenuating circumstances and their overall contribution to
the &quot;greater good&quot; was taken into account.

