Yes it can be both.

Murdering and Killing are not the same thing in society. One can kill in
self defense - including war. In a war - the killing is justified BY THE
WAR ITSELF. However - killing for no reason or no good(as defined by
that society) reason is unforgivable.

So - what is unacceptable and unforgivable in normal society is
different in a war. In a war - the elimination of the &quot;EVIL&quot; is
considered &quot;good&quot;.

Remember - the MOM is setting rules (Such as what is unforgivable) in
normal life. While it would be nice if one side could set rules that the
OTHER side MUST follow in a war - but somehow I don't think that is likely.
