&gt; use AK, and then only under extreme, extenuating circumstances.  Also
&gt; witness Harry's mercy at the beginning of DH: not only does he not kill
&gt; Stan, but he merely disarms him!  The presence of magic opens up a new
&gt; spectrum of possibilities for countering personal threats without killing
&gt; and, in some cases, without even causing physical harm.

&gt; (I can perhaps imagine that there some desperate situations in which the
&gt; only option is to use the Imperius Curse, so this one is—maybe—sometimes
&gt; forgivable.  As for the Cruciatus and AK, however, there is no excuse.  The
&gt; Cruciatus in particular has even fewer legitimate uses than the Killing
&gt; Curse.)
">

I can see situations in which both are justifiable.  If the intent is to
capture someone, then a curse that can't be shielded against, such as
Crucio, can disable through a shield, and then on can use a non-lethal
spell to disarm and bind the subject.  AK is really like the use of
deadly force by the police in situations where their life is in danger.
There is often only a part of a second to respond to a threat, and
trying to shoot to disarm is something that requires one aim at, and
hit, a rather smaller target.  If there is enough time, and the shooter
is competent, this may be the method of choice, but when push comes to
shove, shooting at the largest target gives the best chance of living to
tell the tell, which is exactly why police are trained to shoot at the
trunk portion of the subject.  It is not unusual for 'shoot outs' to
expend thirty, or forty rounds during a few seconds, with only one or
two shots hitting the subject.  Massive adrenaline flows render most
people quite unable to aim a handgun with any reliability, so you go for
the largest target, and maybe hit that once, if you are lucky.
I have a friend who was shot twice in such a shootout, neither of which
was life-threatening, and he got off 5 shots at the suspect, wounding
him once.  So, about 10 shots were expended at close range (under 30
feet), and only three hit anyone.  That's really better than the usual
situation.
So, using the AK for Harry was a desperation attempt to save his own life.
